Supervised learning
 The algorithms are trained on labeled data.
Goal : To learn a mapping function that can predict the output for new, unseen input data.
Needs to learn by example.
This type of algo uses training data to help determine the patterns and relationships btn the i/ps and the o/ps.

Types of supervised learning 
 1. Classification 
 2. Regression

 Classification 
  used to assign labels or categories to new, unseen data instances based on a trained model.
  The model is trained on labeled dataset, where each instance is already assigned to a known class or category.

  Goal: To learn patterns from the training data and use them to predict the class or category for new unlabeled data instances.

Ex :
 Fraud detection
 Image classification
 Customer retention
 Diagnostics

 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Regression 
   Used for predicting continuous or numerical values based on one or more i/p var.
  It is used to model the relationship btn a dep var (the value to be predicted) and one or more indp var (the fts or i/ps used for predication).

  Ex:
Advertising popularity prediction
Weather forecasting
Market forecasting
Estimating life expectancy
Population growth prediction
